      <name>1. osm_way_295041873</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> likely_destroyed confidence 0.75<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before image, a multi-story building with a reddish-brown roof is clearly visible within the candidate footprint. In the after image, the structure is absent and replaced by a debris-toned patch consistent with rubble/collapse. The footprint shape is no longer discernible as a building; only an irregular ground texture remains within the outlined area.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> Lower resolution and pixelation of the post-event chip make it difficult to confirm whether the structure fully collapsed versus being reduced to a low rubble pile. Some adjacent tree cover in the before image could partially mask a still-standing low remnant, and the resolution gap limits confidence from ~0.85 to 0.75.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.47229245,-66.95783665'>open</a>]]></description>
      <Point><coordinates>-66.95783665,10.47229245,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
      <name>2. osm_way_295041879</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> likely_destroyed confidence 0.55<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before image, the outlined footprint clearly contains a multi-story apartment building with visible roof, walls, and cast shadow. In the after image, the same footprint area appears as a dark, uniform, featureless patch with no discernible building structure, roofline, or walls. The surrounding context buildings remain visible, indicating the dark area is localized to the candidate footprint rather than an imaging artifact covering the whole scene.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> The after image has substantially lower resolution and a hazy, low-contrast appearance which could partially mask a damaged but still partially standing structure. However, the complete absence of any visible roofline, wall, or vertical structure within the footprint, combined with a localized dark patch distinct from surroundings, strongly suggests collapse or destruction. Confirmation requires higher-resolution post-event imagery.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.4715085,-66.95753835'>open</a>]]></description>
      <Point><coordinates>-66.95753835,10.4715085,0</coordinates></Point>
