      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> likely_destroyed confidence high<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before chip, a clear cross/plus-shaped multi-section apartment building with distinct roof structure, rooftop elements, and shadowed relief is visible within the OSM footprint. In the after chip, the same footprint contains no discernible building structure, roofline, or shadows — only ground/vegetation texture consistent with the surrounding cleared area. Adjacent buildings outside the footprint remain visible in the after scene, indicating the loss is footprint-specific rather than a scene-wide data gap.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> Some uncertainty remains because the after image resolution is limited and the building is large, so a low rubble pile could in theory be hidden under vegetation tone. However, the complete absence of shadows, rooflines, and any bright rubble signature within the footprint, contrasted with a clearly intact building just outside, makes a &#x27;likely_destroyed&#x27; call well supported.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.433707041666667,-66.97118965833333'>open</a>]]></description>
