      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> possible_major_damage confidence 0.45<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before image, a clearly visible rectangular multi-section building with a light-colored roof sits within the yellow footprint. In the after image, no building roof or structure is visible within the footprint; the area appears as a flat, bare surface with a small light-colored feature (possibly debris) to the right of the outline. Adjacent buildings to the north remain visible and appear intact in the after image.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> Although the candidate building appears to have disappeared and neighboring buildings remain visible, the dramatic loss of vegetation across the entire scene, reduced resolution, and different color characteristics of the after image raise the possibility of a scene-mismatch or seasonal/sensor change rather than destruction. The footprint area is conspicuously clean with no obvious rubble pile, which is atypical for a collapsed multi-unit apartment block. Cannot confidently distinguish between total destruction, post-event clearing, or imagery/alignment issues.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.5020586,-66.94583539999999'>open</a>]]></description>
